_:ce9cc38cef9827025a967287f8b16b27 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "\n                He was invited to the court of Mǝnilǝk II in 1865. His first, common-law,\n                 wife gave birth to their son Yǝlma Mäkwännǝn. In 1876, he married\n                 Yašimmabet ʾAli, who gave birth to Tafari.\n                 In 1876 Makʷannǝn Walda Mikāʾel became bālāmbārās and in\n                 1881 he joined a campaign against the Oromo.\n                 After the conquest of Ḥarar, he was awarded the rank of\n                 daǧǧāzmāč and became the governor of the region. In 1887\n                 Makʷannǝn Walda Mikāʾel started the imperial expansion to the east and south of\n                 Ḥarar and conquered the parts of ʾOgāden,\n                 as well as parts of the territories of Gadabuursi and\n                 ʿIssa. Makʷannǝn Walda Mikāʾel had good relations with expatriates and lead Ethiopian missions abroad. In\n                 1890 he participated in the Ethio-Italian debates, and in 1895-1896 in the Italian war. In\n                 1902 he represented Mǝnilǝk II at the coronation of\n                 Edward VII in London.\n                " .
<https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6567Makwanne> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P4_has_time_span> _:ce9cc38cef9827025a967287f8b16b27 ;
